@Kapool
FWIW I have an 80s WAM (Go8) and was rejected by Allens. I’m all for the process being as holistic and meritocratic as possible, but we’re talking about the top-of-top tiers here. Firms like Allens have the pulling power to choose from a range of 76+WAM-social-butterfly-unicorns who tick every box that Allens want ticked.
This process is demoralising enough and coming into it with any sense of entitlement or expectations about what individual firms owe you is only going to make life miserable.
